Logging for transparency: This week, I had two expense claims for Vectral Systems that were incorrectly rejected due to a glitch in the new auto-categorization tool. Both have been manually approved. Rachel Whitfield from Vectral HR is informed and displeased — I've apologized and assured her that we are looking into the matter. 

The engineering team is currently investigating the root cause in #engineering. I'm flagging this here in case other account managers encounter similar problems with pilot clients. 

@David — Just a heads up since this is affecting client trust on the Vectral account.

Created OPS-342 to track the Heartland Q1 dispute end-to-end: *Vendor invoice reconciliation — Heartland Movers Q1 2026*

First 3 items on the checklist are done (Airtable verification, cancellation evidence, Swift confirmation). Remaining items are pending Heartland's response to Marcus's dispute email. I'll follow up with Jake on April 1 if we don't hear back — given he never replied to either cancellation email in February, I'm not holding my breath.

@Marcus @Hana you're both tagged on the ticket for visibility.

Noted, Hana. Good to have this flagged early. The $2,650 surcharge approval is the one to watch — if it slips past April 7 we could have vendor commitments at risk right before the April 10 pickup for Webb.

@catalina.dubois — if Patricia hasn't responded by EOD April 7, please escalate by phone. We can't have the cold-chain freight unbooked 72 hours before the Detroit pickup.

I'll keep INV-2026-0401 in the outstanding AR tracker at the full $9,210 for now. Let me know when you get confirmation and I'll note the surcharge lines as approved.
